			<h3 ><a href="#p139310">Re: Items to increase Magic resistance ?</a></h3>
			<p class="author"><a href="./viewtopic.php?p=139310#p139310"><img src="./styles/prosilver/imageset/icon_post_target.gif" width="11" height="9" alt="Post" title="Post" /></a>by <strong><a href="./memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=3003">Ishana</a></strong> &raquo; May 2nd, '08, 05:15 </p>

			

			<div class="content">No, lowering your charm pet's resistance to magic will greatly increase the durations of your charms, not your own stats.  The best thing to do is use tash and fight mobs that cast malo, although you will often have malo on yourself which prevents you from going into out of combat regen if you need it.</div>

			

