			<h3 ><a href="#p139318">Re: Items to increase Magic resistance ?</a></h3>
			<p class="author"><a href="./viewtopic.php?p=139318#p139318"><img src="./styles/prosilver/imageset/icon_post_target.gif" width="11" height="9" alt="Post" title="Post" /></a>by <strong><a href="./memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=369">sunamae</a></strong> &raquo; May 2nd, '08, 15:01 </p>

			

			<div class="content">I personally hate fighting malo mobs because they malo me!  I don't usually care about them landing spells as much as the lack of being able to kick into mana regeneration mode.  Anywho, the principle is correct.  The primary thing you can do is lower their mana resistance via tash (and malosiwhatever if you have a shaman/mage with you), the next most important is getting Total Domination (the charm improving AA), the third tier is Charisma which has a comparatively minor effect (and coincidentally can be rearranged to &quot;is a charm&quot; [I use far too many parenthesis (really I do [I think I've had too much coffee])]).  I suppose you could also count comparative level though that is really a function of magic resistance.  And unless you figure out a way to charm yellow/reds or for some reason are charming greens won't be a major factor in pet selection.  That's it as far as making charm itself work well, other than working on techniques such as staying at max spell casting range, etc.<br /><br />Sunamae<br />7th Hammer</div>

			

		</div>

		
